                        <interp inst="t18360613-name-171" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES STOCKFORD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I produce a certificate of the prisoner's former conviction, which I got from Mr. Clark's office—I was present at the trial, in the September session, 1834—he is the man men<lb></lb>tioned in the certificate (<hi rend="italic">read.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I am not the person, there are many other people of my name. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I am certain of him—I was a witness in the case.</p>
